&lt;p&gt;Obligo is a fast-growing FinTech / Real Estate Tech startup on a mission to build trust between renters and landlords worldwide. &lt;br&gt;We’re looking for a talented Product Manager to join our energetic TLV team and help shape the future of deposit-free renting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a Platform Product Manager to lead the systems, integrations, and internal capabilities that support our products across multiple channels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is focused on building and evolving the foundation behind the product - the APIs, workflows, data models, configurations, and partner integrations that make the overall system scalable, consistent, and easier to extend over time. You’ll work closely with engineering and cross-functional product teams to ensure we are building strong platform capabilities that support both current needs and future growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What you’ll own&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Core platform capabilities that support multiple product experiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Third-party and PMS integrations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;API design and system contracts across internal services and external partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Internal tools and configuration layers that support operations and product scalability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shared workflows and data models across product areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Platform quality, scalability, and long-term maintainability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and evolve platform capabilities in close partnership with engineering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape APIs, workflows, and data models that are scalable, reusable, and reliable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive consistency across integrations and system behaviors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with product managers to ensure feature development is supported by strong underlying platform foundations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate product and business needs into structured platform solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify bottlenecks, inconsistencies, and manual processes, and turn them into scalable systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Balance near-term delivery needs with long-term platform health&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve the way internal teams interact with and operate the platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of product management experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working on platform, infrastructure, or integration-heavy products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical fluency and comfort working on backend, system, and data flow problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience partnering closely with engineering on technical design and implementation tradeoffs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to simplify complexity and turn broad problems into clear, scalable solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with external systems, third-party integrations, or multi-system environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Nice to have&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in payments, fintech, or operationally complex systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building internal tools, configuration systems, or workflow products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What success looks like&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;New integrations are easier and faster to implement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Platform capabilities are reused across products instead of rebuilt each time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Internal teams have better tools and fewer manual workarounds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The system becomes easier to maintain, extend, and scale as the business grows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
