&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In Person in New York City, NY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Obligo&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Obligo is a fast-growing FinTech / Real Estate Tech startup on a mission to build trust between renters and landlords worldwide. By leveraging open banking, data, and AI, Obligo eliminates traditional security deposits and replaces them with a fair, flexible, and transparent renter experience while streamlining operations and reducing risk for property managers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Obligo, we believe that clear communication, thoughtful user experience, and trust-building design are just as important as strong risk models and technical execution. We build financial products that people can understand, trust, and feel confident using.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Obligo is looking for a Vice President of Marketing to lead our marketing strategy and execution as we scale the business and expand our market presence. This is a strategic and hands-on leadership role responsible for driving growth, shaping our brand, and ensuring that Obligo’s story is told clearly, credibly, and consistently across all audiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will own Obligo’s end-to-end marketing function, including brand and positioning, demand generation, product marketing, and lifecycle engagement. You will work closely with Sales, Product, Risk, and the executive team to drive measurable business impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Marketing Strategy &amp;amp; Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Define and lead Obligo’s marketing vision and strategy in alignment with company goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, manage, and mentor a high-performing marketing team&lt;br&gt;Establish clear KPIs and ensure marketing initiatives drive pipeline growth, adoption, and revenue.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a core member of the leadership team, contributing to company-wide strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Growth &amp;amp; Demand Generation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own pipeline generation across channels including paid, organic, content, partnerships, events, and ABM.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Sales on ICP definition, go-to-market strategy, and funnel optimization&lt;strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use data, experimentation, and attribution to improve CAC, conversion rates, and ROI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scale marketing programs across SMB, mid-market, and enterprise segments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brand, Product &amp;amp; Storytelling&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own Obligo’s brand identity, positioning, and messaging across all touchpoints&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead product marketing efforts including launches, narratives, competitive positioning, and sales enablement.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex fintech concepts into clear, compelling, and trustworthy value propositions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lifecycle, Trust &amp;amp; User Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee renter- and customer-facing marketing communications.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build lifecycle programs that drive adoption, engagement, retention, and trust&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Product and UX to ensure a cohesive and consistent customer experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partnerships, PR &amp;amp; External Presence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead PR, communications, industry events, and thought leadership initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support strategic partnerships through co-marketing and joint go-to-market efforts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
